04:51.759 --> 04:53.993
Hey, I called dibs on
the last jelly donut.

04:53.995 --> 04:55.559
Uh, you can't call dibs.

04:55.561 --> 04:57.162
- Can, too.
- Says who?

04:57.164 --> 04:58.163
Says her.

04:58.165 --> 04:59.864
And who died
and made her boss?

05:01.034 --> 05:02.167
Welch, come on.

05:02.169 --> 05:04.235
Finders keepers.
Don't be a dick.

05:04.237 --> 05:06.204
Guys, it's just a donut, let's
not make a beef of this, too.

05:06.206 --> 05:08.206
Rookies should be seen
and not heard.

05:14.847 --> 05:15.879
You okay?

05:15.881 --> 05:18.448
Mmm. Mmm.

05:18.450 --> 05:19.582
Welch, what up?

05:19.584 --> 05:21.985
Shave cream?
What?

05:21.987 --> 05:24.188
You put shave cream
in my donut?

05:24.190 --> 05:25.422
No, it must have just gone bad.

05:25.424 --> 05:26.924
Donuts don't go bad.

05:28.760 --> 05:31.260
This means war.

05:43.975 --> 05:45.607
Morning, Baez.

05:49.546 --> 05:50.678
Comfortable?

05:50.680 --> 05:52.780
Sergeant Bannon,
Internal Affairs.

05:52.782 --> 05:54.582
I, uh...

05:54.584 --> 05:56.684
I need a couple minutes.

05:58.121 --> 06:01.089
Well, the boss ain't in.
Why don't we go in his office?

06:09.665 --> 06:12.066
So where'd you take
Ellen Turner last night?

06:12.068 --> 06:14.534
Witnesses put her
in your car

06:14.536 --> 06:16.536
leaving the racket
for Detective Vandenberg.

06:16.538 --> 06:17.404
Witnesses?

06:17.406 --> 06:18.672
People saw you.

06:18.674 --> 06:19.840
You saying they didn't?

06:19.842 --> 06:21.241
What's this about?

06:21.243 --> 06:23.743
Her son says
she didn't come home last night.

06:23.745 --> 06:25.845
And then she left a message,
also last night, for IA,

06:25.847 --> 06:27.680
said to expect her
at 8:00 this morning,

06:27.682 --> 06:29.615
said it was urgent.
She never showed up.

06:31.152 --> 06:34.020
So, you tell me,
what's this all about?

06:34.022 --> 06:35.588
Don't know.
Gave her a ride home.

06:35.590 --> 06:36.856
I used to know her, we
talked about the job.

06:36.858 --> 06:38.323
That's it.
That's it?

06:38.325 --> 06:39.457
Yeah, that's it.

06:39.459 --> 06:42.094
I mean, did I watch
her walk in the door?

06:42.096 --> 06:43.262
No. I drove off.

06:43.264 --> 06:44.562
She say she was planning
to meet someone?

06:44.564 --> 06:45.563
Any plans at all?

06:45.565 --> 06:47.432
Not that she told me about.

06:47.434 --> 06:48.333
Uh-huh.

06:48.335 --> 06:50.602
What does that mean? “Uh-huh”?

06:50.604 --> 06:52.237
I'm just looking
for something helpful.

06:52.239 --> 06:54.372
Well, I swear to you,
I'm trying to be helpful.

06:54.374 --> 06:56.640
I don't know how much you know
about former Detective Turner,

06:56.642 --> 06:58.575
but she's lead
kind of a complicated life.

06:58.577 --> 06:59.911
Yeah, I gathered that.

06:59.913 --> 07:02.947
Okay. Has this turned into
a missing persons case?

07:02.949 --> 07:03.981
Not yet.

07:03.983 --> 07:05.116
I mean,
it wouldn't be the first time

07:05.118 --> 07:06.083
she didn't make it home.

07:06.085 --> 07:07.318
If you know what I'm saying.

07:07.320 --> 07:10.054
But I'll reach out
and see if I can find her.

07:11.823 --> 07:13.689
Let me know
if you find anything.

07:20.832 --> 07:24.832
